        <h1 class="section-heading">Laura's Story</h1>
        <!--Section description-->
        <p class="lead section-description text-left black-text">
            “It was completely a God idea,” says Clothe Our Kids Co-Founder Laura Mayer. 
            Never did she imagine what started out as an idea in her garage would turn into a national non-profit reaching thousands of children.
        </p>
        <p class="section-description text-left black-text">
            On November 13, 2013, Laura was cleaning out her children’s outgrown clothing and simply voiced, “Lord, I wish I knew someone who needed these clothes so I could give them away.” 
            Immediately the thought, “Call the school,” dropped in her heart. She called and found out there was a real need in her school and often children would go without basic necessities like socks and undies, have shoes taped together, or own only 1 pair of pants.  
            Hanging up the phone, Laura felt the need to help with this problem. Her first thought was to organize a school clothing drive but realized the school would be burdened for space to store items. 
            Then it happened. Laura describes the next moment as feeling as though God “downloaded” the idea to start this organization, call it Clothe Our Kids, and work as a resource for local school teachers and counselors. 
            That it would be a way to show these children His love and compassion, and provide confidence-building clothes and shoes to children in need. 
            Laura felt as though God had laid the plan in front of her but gave her the choice whether to obey. She is so happy she said yes.
        </p>

        <div class="streak streak-photo streak-section" style="background-image:url('../../Content/img/TennesseeCOK/FAQ.jpg')">
            <div class="flex-center white-text rgba-black-strong">
                <ul class="mb-0 list-unstyled">
                    <li><h2 class="h2-responsive"><i class="fa fa-quote-left" aria-hidden="true"></i>Lord, I wish I knew someone who needed <br class="d-none d-md-block" /> these clothes so I could give them away.<i class="fa fa-quote-right" aria-hidden="true"></i></h2></li>
