        <p class="section-description text-left black-text">
            Later that afternoon, Laura called her friend Shelley Lyon to share with her the plan to start Clothe Our Kids, and ask her to help. 
            Shelley immediately said yes and went on to explain that she had felt a tugging on her heart to help area children in need but had not known how to go about such. 
            Laura and Shelley announced their plans to friends and Clothe Our Kids was born. Within 8 weeks, Clothe Our Kids had outgrown the space in Laura’s garage and moved into a borrowed building downtown. 
        </p>

        <p class="section-description text-left black-text">
            What started in 2013 as a single operation in Lincoln County, TN, has grown to include 6 chapter locations in 2 states and has served thousands of children.
        </p>


        <p class="section-description text-left black-text">
            In 2018, Laura Mayer, along with Brandi Breeden, Chapter Director of Clothe Our Kids of North Alabama, started Clothe Our Kids Foundation. 
            COKF is a non-profit organization whose mission is to start Clothe Our Kids chapters all over the United States. 
            They do this by offering start-up grants, on-going director training and support, and traveling to share this vision that is changing the lives of children. 
        </p>

        <p class="section-description text-left black-text">
            More growth is in the plans. If you are interested in learning more about starting a Clothe Our Kids Chapter in your community, email the Foundation at clotheourkidsfoundation@gmail.com
        </p>

        <p class="section-description text-left black-text">
            At Clothe Our Kids we truly believe we are "Meeting a Need. Changing a Life."
        </p>

